# Canonical spelling for the identity that maintains this repository.
#
# A squash merge records the GitHub profile display name rather than the local git
# config, so a merged pull request can land under a different spelling of the same
# person than a local commit does. These entries collapse those spellings.
#
# Every mapping here stays within one identity. Mapping one identity onto another
# would misstate who wrote the code, so it is never done.

athexweb3 <athexweb3@gmail.com> Athex Web3 <athexweb3@gmail.com>
athexweb3 <athexweb3@gmail.com> <athexweb3@users.noreply.github.com>
